FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1772561167
OL,3,CThe big spring switch-on: sunshine,
OL,4,Clonger days and nature's big comeback
OL,6,FNights may still turn chilly under
OL,7,Fclear skies ` that's typical for this
OL,8,Ftime of year ` but by day there'll be
OL,9,Fa real sense of seasonal change.
OL,11,FWhy does everything suddenly feel
OL,12,Fbrighter?
OL,14,FBecause it quite literally is! We're
OL,15,Fnow in meteorological spring and
OL,16,Fdaylight hours are increasing rapidly.
OL,17,FIn fact we're gaining several minutes
OL,18,Fof daylight every day (around 20-30
OL,19,Fminutes a week), with sunsets getting
OL,20,Flater and mornings brighter.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
